title: Jake Hall and Missé Beqiri spark split rumours as they unfollow each other on social media
text:

Reality TV couple Jake Hall and Missé Beqiri have sparked rumours they've secretly split by unfollowing each other on social media.

Towie star Jake, 29, and Real Housewives of Cheshire castmember Missé, 33, got engaged in May 2018 and have a two-year-old daughter, River, together

However, they haven't been pictured together since August and they now appear to have vanished from each other's social media feeds.

Missé last shared a picture of in May, with the Towie star's last snap of her came at his birthday party on August 20.

The disappearing act prompted speculation among fans that the couple have secretly parted ways.

One wrote: "Has Jake and Misse split up?...

Another added: "Such a shame you are no longer together Jake and Misse...

(Image: Instagram)

A third commented on the fact that Jake no longer appears in her pictures, writing: "No signs of Jake."

As well as the social media absence, Misse has posted a number of cryptic messages hinting at a split.

One of them stated: "I hope the truth will bless you as much as your act on social media."

The split rumours come 10 months after the couple's romance hit a major bump when Jake was issued with a restraining order forcing him not to contact Missé for 28 days.

(Image: Instagram)

(Image: akehall01/Twitter)

The order was handed out in December 2018, and no details were given about the reasons it was issued but Jake's lawyer explained that no physical violence had taken place.

The pair got together in November 2016, after Jake split from his longtime Towie girlfriend Chloe Lewis.

They welcomed their first child together, River, a year later in November 2017.

Missé also has a son, Julian ,with her footballer ex-husband Anders Lindegaard.

Mirror Online has contacted a representative for Jake for comment.
